\section{Discussion}
Macachor’s formula extends the Lorentz force law by embedding thermal plasma corrections and quantum tunneling probabilities. This allows for higher ionization efficiency in hydrogen plasma, resonance tuning with external energy fields, and closed-vacuum operation, bypassing gravitational and relativistic constraints.

\section{Conclusion}
Macachor’s Quantum Mechanics Formula for EM Plasma Hydrogen Propulsion represents the next evolutionary step in plasma propulsion. By uniting electromagnetism, plasma dynamics, and quantum mechanics under a scalar-embedded framework, it provides a scientifically grounded pathway toward photonic-speed propulsion and the transition to energy-based civilizations.

